\markdownSetup{htmlOutput=commonmark}
<<<
This test ensures that the `htmlOutput` option produces individual
renderers for each CommonMark HTML block type.

<!-- block comment -->

<script>alert('hi')</script>

<div>
hello
</div>

foo <b>bar</b> baz
>>>
BEGIN document
codeSpan: htmlOutput
softLineBreak
interblockSeparator
inputBlockHtmlCommentElement: b3ffb66dd7e08481fe6b45f4a11c8552.verbatim
interblockSeparator
inputBlockHtmlSpecialElement: dba3735d95b8e26c1629e504c873955b.verbatim
interblockSeparator
inputBlockHtmlRegularElement: 5ed18adb8bdfa2141d18971defaa62ac.verbatim
interblockSeparator
inlineHtmlOpenTag: <b>
inlineHtmlCloseTag: </b>
END document
